<p><span><em>The Brave and The Bold</em> #28</span> (March, 1960) featured the first appearance of the 
			<a href="../teams/dc/JLA.php" target="_blank">Justice League of America</a>.</p><br />

			<p>Modeled after the <a href="../teams/dc/JSA.php" target="_blank">Justice Society of America</a> from the 1940's, the JLA initially 
			featured some of DC Comics' popular second-string characters, eventually adopting the publisher's two most popular 
			characters, <a href="../heroes/dc/BatmanI.php" target="_blank">Batman</a> and <a href="../heroes/dc/Superman.php" target="_blank">Superman</a>.</p><br />